title: For Sale:  High Power Sporting Rifle Course (March 2nd & 3rd 2018)
postcontent: The High Power Sporting Rifle Course (March 2 to 3, 08:00 AM to 5:00 PM) is designed to train and safely qualify a shooter with a centerfire rifle weighing less than 9.5 pounds, including detachable magazines and sights may be used. Telescopic and reflex/red-dot sights are permitted, slings are excluded. Examples of rifles include AR-15 Series, most bolt action sporting rifles, M1A/M-14, Military Surplus Battle Rifle, AK Variant, Ruger Mini 14 and similar rifle, LE Patrol Rifle like Remington or Keltec. Any equipment that is considered usual and customary for field use, such as coats with light padding at the shoulder/elbow and unpadded gloves, may be used. Special jackets, gloves, slings, set triggers, hooked butt plates, palm rests and other devices associated with formal competition shooting are prohibited. Shooters will be taught the fundamentals of Marksmanship, definitions and terminology associated with ballistics, proper sighting methods, shooting positions and target engagement techniques. Shooters are required to bring a minimum of 100 rounds of the same type and manufacture of ammunition, EG: 100 HPBT 168 Grain 308 WIN or 100 Soft Point 55 Grain .223 REM. Target or match grade ammunition is preferred, however ball and hunting ammunition is authorized but not recommended. Appropriate range gear such as range bag with cleaning kit, specialty tools, eye & hearing protection, spotting scope or binoculars, note pad and pen/pencil, shooting mat, rain gear, sunscreen, water and snacks. Timeline will include:Day 1 - 4 hours of classroom instruction, 1 hour break followed by 4 hours range instruction.Day 2 - 4 hours familiarization with target / instructor feedback and pre-qualification, 1 hour break followed by qualification, After Action Review and qualification presentation. Cost of course is $175.00. Class capacity is 6 to 1 student to instructor ratio. The more students the more instructors with added depth of experience.This is not a sniper or designated marksman class. This is not a 1000 yard competition. This class is designed to teach the average shooter how to get the most out of their gun and realize the rifles capabilities and the shooters individual potential. And mostly have fun. postcontent: U.S. Military and Vintage/Surplus Military High Power Rifle Qual Course (April 27th, 2018, 08:00 AM to 5:00 PM). This course will cover the typical use and qualification of Any safe U.S. military service rifle, vintage/surplus battle rifle and soviet block centerfire rifle with metallic sights. A sling may be used in all positions except standing. Internal 5, 8 or 10 round box magazine or a 10-, 20- or 30-round detachable magazine may be used. Hook butt plates and palm rests are not permitted. 120 rounds are required for this course. Any ammunition except tracer, armor piercing and incendiary ammunition is permitted. Shooters must bring a range bag with safety gear (eye & ear protection) any required sight tools, cleaning equipment, magazines or striper clips, sunscreen, wet weather gear and bottle of water. Shooters will be taught the fundamentals of classic Infantry Marksmanship and will be firing on a 100 yard/meter range while engaging targets in the Standing, Kneeling/Sitting, Prone un-Supported and Prone Supported at simulated distances of 200, 300, 500 and 600 yards/meters on scaled targets. Course will begin with 1 hour block on shooting fundamentals, 1 hour block on shooting positions, 1 hour block on zeroing rifle sights and one hour zeroing rifles. Break for lunch for one hour then resume in the PM with prequalification and Instructor & target feedback, then with qualification, after action review and qualification presentation. Student to instructor ratio is 6 to 1. The more shooters present the more instructors with varied and additional experience can be available. Cost of course is $100.00.
